  'Trawling is a common fishing method that involves a boat - trawler - pulling a fishing net through the water behind it. Trawling lasts as long as the vessel is sailing in a fishing area, its speed is within the expected bounds
for a trawling activity and it is sailing in a manner that is typical for a trawling activity. Trawling activities cannot be arbitrarily brief, i.e., the duration of trawling activities exceeds a minimum temporal threshold.'

